description: Dean Norton’s lecture is an entertaining look at the gardening world of George Washington. As the Director of Horticulture at Mount Vernon, Norton oversees the preservation of the most accurate 18th century gardens and landscapes in America, including the most recently restored pleasure garden. For over 150 years people have studies, researched and dug in the earth for clues about George Washington’s home. Ticketed event.
tags: Dean Norton, George Washington, gardening, horticulture, 18th century gardens, lecture
title: Dean Norton “Welcome Home, George Washington”
